Sentencas: Ceramic injection molding is an economically and environmentally interesting technique to produce the support layers for anode supported solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Near net shape manufacturing of planar anode supported solid oxide fuel cells by using ceramic injection molding and screen printing

Sentencas: We investigated if this technique can be used for the support layer of manufacturing of planar AS-SOFCs in sizes of 50 x 50 and 100 x 100 mm(2).
Titulo: Near net shape manufacturing of planar anode supported solid oxide fuel cells by using ceramic injection molding and screen printing

Sentencas: After setting the injection molding parameters, we could make 60 near net shape substrates per hour under semi-automatic conditions.
Titulo: Near net shape manufacturing of planar anode supported solid oxide fuel cells by using ceramic injection molding and screen printing

Sentencas: Screen printing was used to apply the Ni-YSZ anode functional layer, 8YSZ electrolyte, 10GDC barrier layer and LSCF cathode.
Titulo: Near net shape manufacturing of planar anode supported solid oxide fuel cells by using ceramic injection molding and screen printing

Sentencas: An electrochemical test on a 50 x 50 mm(2) cell revealed a maximum power density of 1.25 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. SEM investigations have shown that the injection molded support layer adheres well to the screen printed anode functional layer, and that the anode support layer possesses a homogeneous microstructure.
Titulo: Near net shape manufacturing of planar anode supported solid oxide fuel cells by using ceramic injection molding and screen printing

Sentencas: This shows that ceramic injection molding is a viable technique to economically produce planar AS-SOFCs at industrial scale.
Titulo: Near net shape manufacturing of planar anode supported solid oxide fuel cells by using ceramic injection molding and screen printing
